/* 02_hash128.sql.in — BLAKE3-128-truncated entity hash convenience.
 *
 * Per ADR 0015 + STANDARDS.md "Hash discipline": hashes are bytea(16)
 * end-to-end; never hex, never text. Per RULES.md R22 (use existing
 * types), we do NOT create a parallel `hash128` PG type — bytea with
 * CHECK constraints is the canonical storage. Substrate-specific
 * comparison semantics live in the custom opclass (03_hash128_ops).
 *
 * Real BLAKE3 wrappers (laplace_hash128_blake3, laplace_hash128_merkle)
 * land Chunk 1 Story 1.3 — wrap blake3_hasher_* via liblaplace_core. */

